[[cdo:3 nguŏk 5 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[zh-min-nan:3 goe̍h 5 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[zh-yue:三月初五]] {{Lunisolar March}} '''March 5''' is the 5th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|12=draft}}.
== Events == * [[中平]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[184]] {{ill|April 2|ja|4月2日}}) – The planned simultaneous uprising of the Yellow Turban Rebellion. * [[寛喜]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1229]] {{ill|March 31|ja|3月31日}}) – Due to natural disasters and famine, the era name was changed from {{ill|Antei|ja|安貞}} to {{ill|Kanki|ja|寛喜}}. * [[Ōnin]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1467]] {{ill|April 9|ja|4月9日}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Bunshō|ja|文正}} to {{ill|Ōnin|ja|応仁}}. * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1580]] _月_日) – {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|ja|織田信長}} reached a peace agreement with Ishiyama Hongan-ji; as a result, {{ill|Kōsa|ja|高佐}} withdrew from Ishiyama, effectively ending the 【Ishiyama Campaign|石山合戦】. * [[正徳 (日本)|正徳]] 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1714]] {{ill|April 18|ja|4月18日}}) – The senior retainer of Ōoku, {{ill|Eshima|ja|絵島}}, was exiled to Takato in Shinshū following punishment in the 【Ejima Ikushima Incident|江島生島事件】. * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1840]] {{ill|April 7|ja|4月7日}}) – The 7th-generation kabuki actor {{ill|Ichikawa Danjūrō (7th)|ja|市川團十郎 (7代目)}} gave the first performance of one of kabuki’s 18 repertoire pieces, “{{ill|Kanjin-chō|ja|勧進帳}}.”
== Births == * [[Ryakuō]] 3rd year / [[興国]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1340]] {{ill|April 2|ja|4月2日}}) – {{ill|Ashikaga Mototada|ja|足利基氏}}, the second son of {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|ja|足利尊氏}}, and the first Kamakura Kubō (died [[1367]]). * [[永正]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1511]] {{ill|April 2|ja|4月2日}}) – {{ill|Ashikaga Yoshiharu|ja|足利義晴}}, the 12th shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (died [[1550]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1869]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日}}) – {{ill|Kawakami Bēzan|ja|川上眉山}}, a novelist (died [[1908]]).
== Deaths == * [[元豊 (宋)|元豊]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1085]] {{ill|April 1|ja|4月1日}}) – {{ill|Emperor Shenzong (Song)|ja|神宗}}, the 6th Emperor of the Song dynasty (born [[1048]]). * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1861]] {{ill|April 14|ja|4月14日}}) – {{ill|Utagawa Kuniyoshi|ja|歌川国芳}}, a renowned ukiyo-e artist (born [[1797]]).
