ew from Ishiyama, effectively ending the 【Ishiyama Campaign|石山合戦】. * [[正徳 (日本)|正徳]] 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1714]] {{ill|April 18|ja|4月18日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – The senior retainer of Ōoku, {{ill|Eshima|ja|絵島|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, was exiled to Takato in Shinshū following punishment in the 【Ejima Ikushima Incident|江島生島事件】. * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1840]] {{ill|April 7|ja|4月7日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – The 7th-generation kabuki actor {{ill|Ichikawa Danjūrō (7th)|ja|市川團十郎 (7代目)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} gave the first performance of one of kabuki’s 18 repertoire pieces, “{{ill|Kanjin-chō|ja|勧進帳|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.”
