{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月初五|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 5일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 5''' is the 5th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[中平]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[184]] [[:en:April 2|April 2]]) – The planned simultaneous uprising of the Yellow Turban Rebellion. * [[寛喜]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1229]] [[:en:March 31|March 31]]) – Due to natural disasters and famine, the era name was changed from [[:en:Antei|Antei]] to [[:en:Kangi|Kanki]]. * [[Ōnin]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1467]] [[:en:April 9|April 9]]) – The era name was changed from [[:en:Bunshō|Bunshō]] to [[:en:Ōnin|Ōnin]]. * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 8th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1580]] _月_日) – [[:en:Oda Nobunaga|Oda Nobunaga]] reached a peace agreement with Ishiyama Hongan-ji; as a result, {{ill|Kōsa|ja|高佐|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōsa|qq=}} withdrew from Ishiyama, effectively ending the 【Ishiyama Campaign|石山合戦】. * [[正徳 (日本)|正徳]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1714]] [[:en:April 18|April 18]]) – The senior retainer of Ōoku, {{ill|Eshima|ja|絵島|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eshima|qq=}}, was exiled to Takato in Shinshū following punishment in the 【Ejima Ikushima Incident|江島生島事件】. * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1840]] [[:en:April 7|April 7]]) – The 7th-generation kabuki actor [[:en:Ichikawa Danjūrō VII|Ichikawa Danjūrō (7th)]] gave the first performance of one of kabuki’s 18 repertoire pieces, “[[:en:Kanjinchō|Kanjin-chō]].”
== Births == * [[Ryakuō]] 3rd year / [[興国]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1340]] [[:en:April 2|April 2]]) – [[:en:Ashikaga Motouji|Ashikaga Mototada]], the second son of [[:en:Ashikaga Takauji|Ashikaga Takauji]], and the first Kamakura Kubō (died [[1367]]). * [[永正]] 8th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1511]] [[:en:April 2|April 2]]) – [[:en:Ashikaga Yoshiharu|Ashikaga Yoshiharu]], the 12th shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (died [[1550]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1869]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – [[:en:Bizan Kawakami|Kawakami Bēzan]], a novelist (died [[1908]]).
== Deaths == * [[元豊 (宋)|元豊]] 8th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1085]] [[:en:April 1|April 1]]) – [[:en:Thần Tông|Emperor Shenzong (Song)]], the 6th Emperor of the Song dynasty (born [[1048]]). * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1861]] [[:en:April 14|April 14]]) – [[:en:Utagawa Kuniyoshi|Utagawa Kuniyoshi]], a renowned ukiyo-e artist (born [[1797]]).
